text: Suzanne Moore (born 1958) is an English journalist. Moore was born in Ipswich to an American father and a Tory-voting working-class mother. She is a feminist. She was the winner of the Orwell Prize for Journalism in 2019. 2019 JOURNALISM PRIZE WINNER Suzanne Moore, orwellfoundation.com, accessed 26 November 2020 and resigned from The Guardian in 2020. ==References== Category:1958 births Category:Living people Category:British feminists Category:English journalists Category:People from Ipswich
